"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-culture-2024-0730-1462593-sunday-miscellany-on-a-young-girls-olympic-dreams\", \"text\": \"  A young girl's Olympic dreams, aided by Tarzan (and her dad) - forSunday Miscellanyon RT\\u00c9 Radio 1, listen toOlympic Golds,by Mae Leonard above.  Johnny Weissmuller taught me how to swim.  I am talking about Tarzan of the Apes, but I must give my father some credit too, he had a lot to do with it. After I had been rescued from drowning in the river beside our home in Limerick, dad set about teaching me how to swim...  Listen to more fromSunday Miscellanyhere.    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"